		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd. I. Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Pen</placeName></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>London</placeName> <date>11<hi rend="sup">th</hi> March 1853</date></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>2 Heneags Lane&#44; Bevis<add>&#63;</add> Marks</placeName></p>
			<p>Revd Sir&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">It is with deep regret that I<lb/> inform you of the demise of the <persName>Revd D.<lb/> Meldola</persName> <add>Hebrew</add> which took place rather<lb/> suddenly on <date>Wednesday 2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi></date> Inst.&#44; he<lb/> had been indisposed for about two months<lb/> and a half with a disease of the throat &#38;<lb/> lungs&#44; but no person&#44; not even his medi&#45;<lb/>&#45;cal advisers had an idea that he was<lb/> so near his death. I can assure you<lb/> that he always had a very high opinion<lb/> of you and deservedly so. May I request<lb/> that you will be kind enough to insert<lb/> something in the &#8220;Occident&#8221; concerning<lb/> our departed friend&#44; &#8220;Peace be with him&#8221;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I have sent you the &#8220;Hebrew Observer.&#8221;<lb/> in which you will find an account of the<lb/> funeral.</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">Hoping you are well</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">I remain</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">Revd. Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">yours truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">David Piza</persName></p>
          
